JEFF KINSEY v. STATE OF FLORIDA 15 So. (2nd) 753

June Term, 1943

December 7, 1943 Division A J. R. Kelley, for appellant. J. Tom, Watson, Attorney General, and John G. Wynn, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

Appellant appeals from a conviction of the larceny of two cows. The only question presented under the record is whether the evidence is sufficient. We have read the evidence and find that it fully sustains the verdict of the jury.

Affirmed.

BUFORD, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS, ADAMS and SE-.BRING, JJ., concur. TERRELL and CHAPMAN, JJ., dissent.
